The paper deals with the problem of discovering venues from multimodal data, specifically images and text. This involves tasks such as cross-modal retrieval and deep learning, which are commonly associated with computer vision (cs.CV), information retrieval (cs.IR), and multimedia (cs.MM) research. Additionally, the paper mentions the use of textual descriptions of venues, which suggests a natural language processing (cs.CL) component. Finally, the proposed model involves joint optimization of pairwise and category-based correlations, which is a machine learning (cs.LG) problem.
